Actually liveness checks do fail during testing as well, here's an example for PeerID=`16Uiu2HAmHKj9KTUEUPpw9F3EaDkT6QVXZNTRVerFJJtnkcC5CHgx`, logged when running `TestWakuV2Filter`:
```
2023-09-26T17:54:12.044+0300    INFO    wakuv2/waku.go:1017     wakuv2 filter subscription success      {"peer": "16Uiu2HAmHKj9KTUEUPpw9F3EaDkT6QVXZNTRVerFJJtnkcC5CHgx", "pubsubTopic": "/waku/2/default-waku/proto", "contentTopics": ["/waku/1/0x01020304/rfc26"]}

2023-09-26T17:54:12.930+0300    INFO    wakuv2/waku.go:1077     Check sub aliveness     {"peerId": "16Uiu2HAmHKj9KTUEUPpw9F3EaDkT6QVXZNTRVerFJJtnkcC5CHgx", "topics": ["/waku/1/0x01020304/rfc26"], "subID": "3340285d-5be1-4967-8600-b0d1ab6ffbf4"}

2023-09-26T17:54:12.987+0300    ERROR   node2.filterv2-lightnode        filter/client.go:213    receiving FilterSubscribeResponse {"error": "EOF"}
github.com/waku-org/go-waku/waku/v2/protocol/filter.(*WakuFilterLightNode).request
        /Users/vvlasov/c/status-go/vendor/github.com/waku-org/go-waku/waku/v2/protocol/filter/client.go:213
github.com/waku-org/go-waku/waku/v2/protocol/filter.(*WakuFilterLightNode).Ping
        /Users/vvlasov/c/status-go/vendor/github.com/waku-org/go-waku/waku/v2/protocol/filter/client.go:360
github.com/waku-org/go-waku/waku/v2/protocol/filter.(*WakuFilterLightNode).IsSubscriptionAlive
...
2023-09-26T17:54:12.987+0300    INFO    wakuv2/waku.go:1080     Sub not alive   {"peerId": "16Uiu2HAmHKj9KTUEUPpw9F3EaDkT6QVXZNTRVerFJJtnkcC5CHgx", "subID": "3340285d-5be1-4967-8600-b0d1ab6ffbf4", "error": "EOF"}
```

@pavloburykh looked through logs. Haven't yet managed to precisely locate the issue. There were several stream resets in logs, but these should have been handled properly.

Identified one related problem here: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/4131. Peer ping was not properly working for newly installed filters. Testing it now.

There's another weird problem: aliveness check failures with error message "404 - NOT_FOUND: peer has no subscriptions". Checked one particular case, and the peer in question was not unsubscribed from before the error, so i don't understand what is the problem yet. **UPDATE**: saw in the logs that the peer was disconnected earlier.
